586
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:45,000
[Day four]
was burned by a Heavenly Fire last night.

587
00:32:45,070 --> 00:32:47,230
The report says four people died
in the fire.

588
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:59,280
What should we do?

589
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,560
Go. Call the coroner.

590
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,230
Magistrate,

591
00:33:03,310 --> 00:33:04,830
the coroner suddenly fell ill
two days ago,

592
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:06,400
with a flushed face,
continuous sneezing,

593
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:07,280
and took sick leave at home.

594
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:10,640
Of all times, why now?

595
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:11,920
Let me try.

596
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,230
I know a bit about medicine.

597
00:33:18,230 --> 00:33:19,230
Sure... Take a look.

598
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:33,190
What do you find?

599
00:33:34,190 --> 00:33:35,160
The four bodies

600
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:36,710
are all male.

601
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:41,230
They have calluses on their palms

602
00:33:43,470 --> 00:33:44,560
and purlicues.

603
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,280
They were all burned to death.

604
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,310
I know that!

605
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:56,520
Yeah.

606
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:04,470
Wait.

607
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:06,710
They already were dead

608
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:08,800
before the fire started.

609
00:34:13,430 --> 00:34:14,310
In his mouth,

610
00:34:14,640 --> 00:34:15,520
there's no dust.

611
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:20,640
I'll go into the scene and take a look.

612
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:23,640
You...

613
00:34:24,110 --> 00:34:24,760
Follow him.

614
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,070
Yes.

615
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:39,110
I'll go in the scene, too.

616
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,160
It's burned to a crisp.

617
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:58,230
What kind of clues can we get?

618
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:00,070
Let's just do it.

619
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,000
What did you find?

620
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:27,680
At the murder scene,

621
00:35:27,680 --> 00:35:28,400
anything found

622
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:29,160
must be turned over to the gover...

623
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:30,950
What's wrong?

624
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,830
It's just a bunch of dead silkworms.

625
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:36,310
What's the big deal?

626
00:35:36,590 --> 00:35:38,040
You, go over there and check.

627
00:35:47,950 --> 00:35:51,110
Why these silkworms?

628
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:55,430
What are you doing?

629
00:35:57,470 --> 00:35:58,670
I want to take some silkworms

630
00:35:58,870 --> 00:35:59,670
and check again.

631
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:00,670
No need to do so.

632
00:36:01,390 --> 00:36:02,000
Someone,

633
00:36:02,150 --> 00:36:03,230
take these bodies

634
00:36:03,230 --> 00:36:04,840
and everything we found here

635
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:05,600
back to the office.

636
00:36:05,950 --> 00:36:06,910
Come here. Clean this place up.

637
00:36:06,910 --> 00:36:07,630
Wait...

638
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,000
Magistrate,

639
00:36:09,470 --> 00:36:10,520
let me investigate again.

640
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,520
I'm sure I can find something.

641
00:36:12,950 --> 00:36:14,120
No need to do so.

642
00:36:14,870 --> 00:36:16,630
This case involves the palace.

643
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:17,950
It's out of my hands.

644
00:36:18,430 --> 00:36:19,080
If you want to investigate,

645
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:21,120
go to see the Minister of Justice.

646
00:36:21,430 --> 00:36:21,950
Go.

647
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:22,840
Magistrate,

648
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,600
let me investigate again, please.

649
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:27,000
Today

650
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,520
is the fourth day.

651
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,670
It's hot.

652
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,000
So hot...

653
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,000
It's so hot.

654
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:49,470
Don't you get it?

655
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:52,150
You can't solve this case.

656
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:56,950
It's a clash of giants.

657
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,040
It's so hot.

658
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:01,840
Hurry up.

659
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,000
Let's go.

660
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:04,710
Let's go back and rest.

661
00:37:04,710 --> 00:37:05,670
Let's go. Hurry up.

662
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:06,320
- Yes.
- Yes.

663
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:08,910
Careful.

664
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:10,560
Watch out.

665
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,320
You've got something?

666
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,280
Look ahead. Slow down...

667
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:13,520
Okay.

668
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:16,080
Sure.

669
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,230
That magistrate of Wannian County said

670
00:37:19,230 --> 00:37:20,870
''Why these silkworms?''

